==English==

===Adjective===
'''curve'''
# ''(obsolete):'' Bent without angles; crooked; curved; as, a curve line; a curve surface.

=== Noun ===
'''curve'''  (''plural:'' [[curves]])
# A gentle [[bend]], especially in a road.
# ''(geometry):'' a line without angles that is not straight for any portion; a line that [[slope]]s
# {{slang}}: attractive features of a woman (usually used in the plural sense)

===Verb===
'''to curve'''  ([[curves]], [[curved]], [[curving]])
# To bend; to crook; as, to curve a line; to curve a pipe; to cause to swerve from a straight course; as, to curve a ball in pitching it.
# To bend or turn gradually from a given direction; as, the road curves to the right. 

